obo:UBERON_0002435  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_3116  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Deletion of plexin-D1 dramatically increases mEPSC frequency in direct pathway MSNs\"\nFig.4: \"Deletion of plexin-D1 slightly decreases spine density in direct pathway MSNs\"\nFig.6: \"Postnatal deletion of plexin-D1 perturbs spine density and mEPSC frequency in direct but not indirect pathway MSNs\"\nFig.7: \"Loss of plexin-D1 in direct pathway MSNs selectively increases the strength of thalamostriatal glutamatergic inputs\"\n\nAbstract: \"Here we show that the interaction between the secreted semaphorin 3E (Sema3E) and its receptor Plexin-D1 is a critical determinant of synaptic specificity in cortico-thalamo-striatal circuits in mice. We find that sema3E is highly expressed in thalamostriatal projection neurons whereas, in the striatum, plexin-D1 is selectively expressed in direct pathway medium spiny neurons (MSNs). Despite physical intermingling of the MSNs, genetic ablation of plexin-D1 or sema3E results in functional and anatomical rearrangement of thalamostriatal synapses specifically in direct pathway MSNs without effects on corticostriatal synapses. Thus, our results demonstrate that Sema3E and Plexin-D1 specify the degree of glutamatergic connectivity between a specific source and target within the complex circuitry of the basal ganglia.\"\n\nNote:\n- Complexin-D1 and Sema3A together create a repulsive cue that repel neurons from making a synapse.\n- Because these proteins represent a repulsive cue that causes these neurons NOT to form a synapse, I have refrained from making the annotation to term 'regulation of synapse assembly'. Experimental description: - \"plexin-D1flox/flox (plexin-D1f/f) mice41 and sema3E knock out (sema3E-/-) mice...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3116" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

